There's no real evidence of actual "mass euphoria". Sure, the media was full of crypto stories and a lot of people talked about cryptocurrencies, but there's no actual numbers on how many people actually bought any bitcoin (or other coins).

&#x200B;

IMO, 2% (if that) of "average Joes" actually bought any cryptoccurrency until now. There's still tremendous room  for growth and adoption, which in turn will lead to price increase as well. Hopefully once we're past this price discovery phase, bitcoin will stabilize and it will become a viable store of value & unit of account (+ LN for mass payments = ideal currency) for the masses.

&#x200B;

